&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Clinical Psychologist, Critical Care, Band 8A Full time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Based at Basildon and Broomfield hospitals, Essex.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity is available to join and develop a new psychosocial team that will be supporting critical care across MSE. In addition to this post the team will comprise of a psychological therapist and a clinical nurse specialist. They will work closely with the units and the psychological therapies team to develop roles to support patients and their families as well as staff. The post holder should ideally have experience of working with inpatients, outpatients and staff in a hospital setting. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Supervision and training experience would be an advantage. We are looking for an individual who has worked with trauma and who is enthusiastic to become an integral part of the critical care teams. The individual will be well supported with good clinical supervision and regular contact with the vibrant multidisciplinary psychological therapies team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Selection will be a two stage process. There will be a stage one group interview, Monday 16th November, for the candidates to learn more about their prospective teams, followed by an individual interview, on morning of Thursday 19th November.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMandy GilesJob titlePsychological Therapies Service ManagerEmail addressPsychotherapy.Counselling@meht.nhs.ukTelephone number01245 516874Additional contact informationPlease ask to speak to a member of the senior team for more information&lt;/p&gt;
